, as well as how the nation fights the war on drugs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aDrug abuse -- Government policy -- United States. 0aDrug abuse -- United States -- Statistics. 0aDrug abusexGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aDrug abusezUnited StatesvStatistics. 0aDrug control -- United States -- Statistics. 0aDrug control -- United States. 0aDrug controlzUnited StatesvStatistics. 0aDrug controlzUnited States. 0aUnited States. -- Office of National Drug Control Policy. 4aCriminology : Criminology. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 4aSociology : Alcohol and Drug Studies. 4aSociology : Social Problems. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / Executive Branch.2bisacsh1 aScherlen, Renee G., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143844839840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438448398423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438448398/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles